    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-07T23:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-07T23:54:00-05:00" n="970"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d970">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.515/55: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-08T08:00:00+03:06"
                            >November 8, 1943—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:23 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>174. British Minister here has suggested that the entire 8 million rials
                    mentioned in Department’s 71, September 18 [<hi rend="italic">17</hi>], 11 p.m.,
                    be delivered to Gellatly-Hankey and Co., a British firm for sale to pilgrims.
                        <pb facs="0922" n="910" xml:id="pg_910"/> Local officials object. The second
                    paragraph of Department’s wire appears to support British suggestion because
                    firm named sometimes acts as Government bankers.</p>
                <p>I request authorization to inform local officials that the United States
                    Government did not intend to object to sale being effected by Finance Ministry
                    itself or by such other agent as local Government may choose.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d970fn3">Such authorization was given in telegram No. 99, November
                        11, 4 p.m. (890F.515/53).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
